15/03/2011
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski, who leads the ruling VMRO-DPMNE, meets with Branko Crvenkovski, leader of the main opposition party SDSM, on Tuesday (March 15th) to discuss early elections. 
US Ambassador Philip Reeker hailed the initiative as a step towards resuming political dialogue and ending the opposition's parliamentary boycott. 
The SDSM has set several conditions for holding free and democratic elections, including changes to the electoral code and updating voting lists. 
(Kanal 5, Sitel, Alsat M, Makfax - 14/03/11)
